##Author Fang Fang and her Wuhan Diary: "I'm not being critical. " 

Wechat, chinanewsweekly

Function introduction, here is "China News weekly" the head of the weekly gentleman, the influence has the influence you. Come with me to break through the fog, to find the truth, to watch the Times.

"The outbreak in Wuhan should be under control by now. A change may come at any time. "

-- Xia Chunping, vice president and vice editor, China News Service

The city of Wuhan, which was shut down by the new pneumonia outbreak, has never received as much attention as it does today, and famous writer Fang Fang's Daily "Wuhan Diary" has become an Internet sensation. Its plain language, vivid narrative, true feelings, outspoken style infected every reader, by netizens for fast.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"Wuhan Diary" author, famous writer Fang Fang February 22 in Wuhan, an exclusive interview with China News Service reporters. China News Service, photo by Quan Anhua

Grew up drinking water from the Yangtze River, fang Fang, who is very familiar with the way of life in Wuhan, said in an exclusive interview with a China News Service reporter in Wuhan Today: "I just want to record, you see, a lot of trivial matters. And I didn't plan on writing it down at first. I had no idea how many people would read it. I always thought it was strange."

Stop writing novels and Rewrite "Wuhan Diary"

Speaking of the original intention of writing "Wuhan Diary" , Fang Fang told reporters, affected by the new crown pneumonia epidemic, many people in Wuhan at the moment in suffering, in a fight with death. Not from childhood to old people living in Wuhan, I am afraid it is difficult to have such a mood, it is difficult to understand the pain, but they simply can not help, so her inner trauma. "A lot of people leave messages saying that they feel at ease after reading my diary in Wuhan every day. It really surprises me and gives me a great honor. If so, I would like to write for them every day, " Fang Fang said.

Beginning on the first day of the first lunar month, Fang Fang kept a diary of what he had seen and learned, which he posted online every day. "For people who have been quarantined at home because of the epidemic, literature is weak at this time. But it's important to record what's really going on and what you think, " Fang Fang told reporters. "The fact that there were so many people watching for a few days made me feel scared, and it spread so quickly on the Internet that it made me a bit of a misfit for a niche reader. I almost didn't want to write, but my classmates and friends encouraged me to keep writing until the day the blockade was lifted."

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"Wuhan Diary" author, famous writer Fang Fang (left) in Wuhan on February 22, an exclusive interview with China News Service reporters. China News Service, photo by Quan Anhua

Fang Fang admits she had no idea the Wuhan diary would be so sought after. " 'Wuhan Diary' is just a few bits and pieces, plus a little bit of their own feelings, as well as writing prose as to study the use of words and sentences. Weibo is a place for gossip. It is free to write whatever you want, and it is often filled with errors and omissions. I don't know why people like it so much. I was going to finish a novella during the Spring Festival, but now I can't. My Heart, like so many netizens across the country, is focused on the epidemic, and I can't get down to writing a novel. Writing 'Wuhan Diary' can calm my mind. "

A turning point could come at any moment

Regarding the trend of the epidemic, "The outbreak in Wuhan should be under control now, " Fang Fang said. The epidemic has gone through several stages. One is to go through the panic stage, this stage should be the end of the first day. National Attention, high-level instructions, and help from all over. The people know in their hearts that if it becomes a state operation, the Chinese way, it will be contained. So the people of Wuhan stopped panicking. But unexpectedly, since then a large number of patients began to attack, Wuhan people entered a very painful stage. More and more people are falling ill, hospitals are unable to reach so many people without being prepared, and health care workers are also heavily infected. Those days patients run around, there is no way to save the doctor, the medical staff is about to collapse, this is also the most depressed the most helpless sad stage. It should be said that the change of provinces and cities, as well as the establishment of a shelter hospital, and 19 provinces chi-aid Hubei, this situation slowly eased down. Now there's no way to save the case, now critically ill patients, almost the previous stock. The delay became serious because of the lack of medical treatment. There are a lot of critically ill patients, so the death rate has not come down."

The picture shows the medical staff in the "Shelter Hospital" in the living room of Wuhan. China News Service, photo by Gao Xiang

"With support from all over the country, the Wuhan epidemic is moving toward an inflection point, " Fang Fang said with a long-lost smile. Many of the patients have been discharged from the hospital with smiles on their faces, not fake smiles, but genuine ones, even though they were all over the streets not so long ago, and today they look like they haven't been there for a long time. But with a start like that, won't the smiles soon follow?"

"How wonderful the people of Wuhan are! "

"The people of Wuhan are so kind that they shoulder the burden of disaster in order to let the people of the country live as usual. In general, the people of Wuhan are very cooperative, and it is not easy for them to be locked up in their homes for almost a month, " Fang Fang said. "adults, with good sense, families with children or other non-new coronary diseases, chronic patients who have to be constantly medicated, such as those with leukemia who need dialysis, and those who are stuck outside the city and can not make it back to the city five million times have a hard time, and they are all paying the price for the epidemic. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Couriers sort through arriving packages at a delivery office of a courier company on General Road, Hankou, Wuhan, on Feb. 9. Couriers are busier than usual as a large number of people choose to shop online in the wake of the new pneumonia outbreak. China News Service, photo by Zhang Chang

"The city of Wuhan has been closed for almost a month, but the city of 10 million people is as orderly as ever. I saw four types of people in front of me, the delivery boys, who were still on their bikes; the police, who stood in front of many intersections and hospitals in cold weather, often facing people and carrying out tasks that had to be performed; the community workers at the grass roots, who went from house to house to visit; and the sanitation workers, who did their best to clean the streets, even though there were few pedestrians and only a few leaves on the roads. From the beginning of the epidemic to the present, they have remained in our eyes in a calm manner, quietly calming the hearts of our entire city,"Fang Fang said.

"Even I want a therapist. "

Fang Fang told reporters: "Wuhan, a city of tens of millions of people, has never been 'sealed off' , and the people have never been locked up in their homes for tens of days. ". These people who live in Wuhan almost everyone has a trauma, it is probably not a matter of bypassing. As I wrote in My 'Wuhan Diary' on February 12: 'whether it's a healthy group of people locked up at home, or a patient who has gone through the streets in the cold rain, or a medical staff who saw their loved ones being loaded into body bags and towed away by a car... ' for example, after the epidemic, do you dare to take off your face masks? Do you dare to talk to someone up close? Could be psychosomatic. And the pain of the families of the patients and the families of the deceased should be even deeper. When one day Wuhan will 'unseal' several happy families and several sad families. The citizens who do not get sick will be very happy. After all, they will be free. But the families of the patients and the deceased will certainly be especially sad. The lights will be on thousands of homes, and only one person will be missing. Only you know the pain of losing your family."

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
February 8, is the Lantern Festival, many places in China light up the lights, refuels for Wuhan! Cheer for China! In this photo, cheering signs light up at Wuhan's landmarks. China News Service, photo by Anyuan District

After the outbreak, the government should organize a large number of psychological counseling experts, psychological treatment and humanistic care for Wuhan people, which is very necessary, Fang Fang urged. Some people may not admit that they have a psychological shadow, but in fact, these shadows may be accompanied by a lifetime, the formation of trouble. Severe cases, such as those who have sought medical attention and been hit with a brick wall, can present recurring nightmares. Of course, there must be some professionals to guide people, so that they learn to guide themselves.

"Even I want to find a psychologist to help me with my mental problems. I write 'Wuhan Diary' every day as a way to help myself with my emotional problems, " Fang Fang said.

"I'm not criticizing, I'm reflecting. "

Fang Fang's "Wuhan Diary" is punctuated by occasional bluntness and criticism. As Fang Fang explains, as she wrote in her "Wuhan Diary" on Feb. 4: "If a disaster of this magnitude is too much to bear, it's too much to bear. But even if it is too much to bear, I'll carry it for you, and you'll have to let me scold you, " Fang Fang admitted, in his "diary of Wuhan" He occasionally complains and gently criticizes Wuhan's handling of the earlier outbreak. "If you can't let off a little steam, or even a few words of complaint or reflection, do you really want to drive people crazy? " Fang Fang said.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
CREDIT: Fang Fang.

"I sometimes ask myself that compared with many cities in the world, Wuhan is not a pleasant place, especially with an unpleasant climate. So what would I like about it? Is it its history and culture? Or its customs? Or is it the color of the lake? Actually, none of this is true. The reason I like it is because I'm familiar with it. Because, put all the cities of the world in front of me, but I only know it. It's as if a lot of people are walking towards you, and out of all the strange faces, there's only one face smiling at you, showing you the smile you know, and that face is Wuhan,"Fang Fang told China News Service in an article she wrote years ago, "SHIYUN: There is no place like Jing Ting Mountain. Wuhan is my Jing Ting Mountain. "

"The tone of my 'Wuhan Diary' has always been absolutely consistent with the government, absolutely co-operating with every move the government makes, and trying to help the government convince people who don't understand, and help the government calm the anxious people, " Fang Fang said bluntly. It's just that we differ in the way we write, and we may occasionally come up with a few words of reflection, that's all. Needless to say, the Wuhan outbreak has exposed many problems in the government's governance. "If we reflect, learn from our mistakes, and act on our conclusions, we will not be sorry for the people who died in this epidemic. "

"I am not a critical person, " she said. "I am also very understanding of the difficulties of governance. What I see as bright is also shown in the 'Wuhan Diary' . "

"after the epidemic, people in Wuhan will go back to the way they used to be, " Fang Fang said. "Life is like the Yangtze River. It never stops. ".

Source: China News Service
